This paper deals with the optimization of Degrees-of-Freedom (DoF) in a wireless communication system, specifically the MISO Broadcast Channel (BC) with delayed and imperfect current Channel-State Information at the Transmitter (CSIT). This topic falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new transmission scheme that combines the Maddah-Ali and Tse scheme (MAT) with Zero-Forcing (ZF), which involves signal processing and communication protocols, making it relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI), Communications (cs.COMM), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories.
